{"data":[{"type":"questionAttempts","id":"17566832","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionAttempts/17566832"},"attributes":{"position":0,"marks":1,"score":0,"answeredAt":"2025-09-29T23:49:08+09:30","options":[1],"response":null,"finalizedAt":"2025-09-29T23:49:08+09:30"},"relationships":{"user":{"data":{"type":"users","id":"50098"}},"questionSession":{"data":null},"session":{"data":null},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"18884"}},"bookmark":{"data":null}}}],"included":[{"type":"questions","id":"18884","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questions/18884"},"attributes":{"optionProportions":[0.05,0.09,0.16,0.56,0.15]},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"11617"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"101026"}}}},{"type":"items","id":"11617","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/items/11617"},"attributes":{"contentType":"question"},"relationships":{"content":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"18884"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"83453"}},"tags":{"data":[{"type":"tags","id":"17"},{"type":"tags","id":"67"},{"type":"tags","id":"71"},{"type":"tags","id":"76"},{"type":"tags","id":"11260"},{"type":"tags","id":"11337"},{"type":"tags","id":"11339"},{"type":"tags","id":"12867"}]},"contributions":{"data":[{"type":"contributions","id":"27341"},{"type":"contributions","id":"27342"},{"type":"contributions","id":"34720"}]}},"meta":{"canRevise":false,"canManage":false,"canDelete":false}},{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"101026","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionRevisions/101026"},"attributes":{"stem":"\u003Cp\u003EA general practitioner has been treating a 28-year-old woman for anxiety over the past six months. The patient expresses romantic interest in the doctor and suggests meeting for dinner. \u003C/p\u003E","stemQuestion":"Which one of the following best describes why accepting this invitation would be inappropriate?","responseType":"sba","marks":1,"options":["It breaches patient confidentiality expectations","It compromises clinical objectivity in future care","It creates a dual relationship with conflicting obligations","It exploits the inherent power imbalance in the therapeutic relationship","It risks interfering with therapeutic rapport and treatment outcomes"],"correctOptions":[3],"correctResponses":null,"explanation":"\u003Cp\u003EThe correct answer is that \u003Cstrong\u003Eit exploits the inherent power imbalance in the therapeutic relationship\u003C/strong\u003E. Medical practitioners hold a position of trust and authority over their patients. Any sexual or romantic relationship with a current patient constitutes a serious breach of professional boundaries, regardless of who initiates it or whether the patient consents.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EThe incorrect options, while relevant concerns, are not the primary reason such relationships are prohibited:\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cul\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EIt breaches patient confidentiality expectations\u003C/strong\u003E - While confidentiality might be at risk, this is not the fundamental ethical issue\u003C/p\u003E\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EIt compromises clinical objectivity in future care\u003C/strong\u003E - Though this is true, it is a secondary concern to the power imbalance\u003C/p\u003E\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EIt creates a dual relationship with conflicting obligations\u003C/strong\u003E - While dual relationships are problematic, the power differential is the key ethical concern\u003C/p\u003E\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EIt risks interfering with therapeutic rapport and treatment outcomes\u003C/strong\u003E - Though this may occur, the exploitation of the power imbalance is the primary ethical violation\u003C/p\u003E\u003C/li\u003E\u003C/ul\u003E\u003Cp\u003EMedical practitioners must maintain clear professional boundaries with patients at all times to ensure safe and ethical practice. Even when a patient initiates the relationship, the professional responsibility remains with the doctor to maintain appropriate boundaries.\u003C/p\u003E","optionExplanations":["","","","",""],"learningPoints":["Medical practitioners must not engage in sexual relationships with current patients as this constitutes a serious breach of professional boundaries.","Sexual relationships with patients exploit the power imbalance inherent in the doctor-patient relationship and are unethical.","Professional boundaries protect both patients and practitioners and must be maintained at all times."],"references":["Medical Board of Australia. Sexual boundaries in the doctor-patient relationship. [online]. 2024. [Accessed on 2025 Jan 16]. Available at: https://www.medicalboard.gov.au/codes-guidelines-policies/sexual-boundaries-guidelines.aspx","Medical Board of Australia. Good medical practice: a code of conduct for doctors in Australia [online]. 2020 [Cited 2025 Jan 15]. Available at: https://www.medicalboard.gov.au/codes-guidelines-policies/code-of-conduct.aspx"]},"relationships":{"itemRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"83453"}},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"18884"}},"stemMedia":{"data":[]},"explanationMedia":{"data":[]}}},{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"83453","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/itemRevisions/83453"},"attributes":{"createdAt":"2025-04-29T19:25:15+09:30","updatedAt":"2025-04-29T19:25:16+09:30"},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"11617"}},"content":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"101026"}}},"meta":{"canDelete":false}},{"type":"tags","id":"17","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/17"},"attributes":{"emoji":"\ud83d\ude07","name":"Bioethics","synonyms":null,"description":null,"position":null,"createdAt":null,"updatedAt":null},"relationships":{"group":{"data":{"type":"tagGroups","id":"1"}},"heading":{"data":{"type":"tagHeadings","id":"6"